ADDITIONAL INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY NOTICE
(Supplemental to Apache 2.0 — not a modification of its terms)

The material concept described in this repository — hereinafter referred
to as "Q-HEAT" (Quantum-screened High-Entropy Aerogel Thermal facade
coating) — including but not limited to:

  (i)  the concept of embedding correlated transition-metal dopant-pair
       centers into a porous high-entropy ceramic/aerogel insulation matrix
       for the purpose of tuning mid-infrared emissivity and solar-thermal
       response of building facade systems;

  (ii) the specific four-qubit reduced active-space electronic model
       formulation for dopant-pair motif screening in facade materials;

  (iii) the Q-HEAT proxy scoring methodology for ranking dopant-pair
        electronic motifs based on bond order, double occupancy, and
        charge imbalance;

is the original invention of:

    Sam Mohammad
    sammohammadwork@gmail.com
    First public disclosure: 2026-05-20 (GitHub commit timestamp)

This public disclosure constitutes DEFENSIVE PUBLICATION and establishes
prior art under 35 U.S.C. § 102 (US) and equivalent statutes globally.

Nothing in the Apache 2.0 license grants any rights to this material
concept beyond what is expressly granted. The software license covers
the code implementation only.

A provisional patent application on the Q-HEAT material concept and
its quantum simulation methodology is being prepared. All rights
reserved on the material concept pending patent filing.

